column1: # -----START OF METADATA -----
# TITLE: Ranavirus and helminth parasite co-infection in invasive American bullfrogs in the Atlantic Forest; Brazil
# DATE: Published 2024; Collection October 2018 - April 2019; Ranavirus qPCR testing August 2019 - March 2020
# AUTHORS: Drs. Lauren V. Ash; Karla Magalhaes Campiao; Caue Pinheiro Teixeira; Nicholas J. Gotelli
# AUTHOR EMAIL: lvash23@gmail.com
# AUTHOR ADDRESS: University of Vermont; 109 Carrigan Dr; Marsh Life Science; Burlington; VT 05405
# AUTHOR WEBSITE: lvash.github.io
# OWNERSHIP: Drs. Lauren Ash and Karla Magalhaes Campiao
# COLLABORATORS: Caue Pinheiro Teixeira; Dr. Nicholas J. Gotelli

# FUNDING SOURCES: University of Vermont Fabri Fialho and John Wheeler Awards; Coordination for the Improvement of Higher Education Personnel and the Federal University of Paraná; Council for Scientific and Technological Development
# REPOSITORY: https://github.com/lvash/Brazil-Bullfrog-Coinfection
# CITATIONS: NA

# SAMPLING LOCATIONS: We collected; measured; and euthanized 65 specimens of American bullfrogs (Aquarana catesbeiana) sampled from 9 sites across three states of Brazil in the Atlantic Forest biome; Site names are in the column 'Site' with its corresponding 'Town' and Brazilian 'State' columns
# SAMPLING TIMES: Bullfrogs were collected October 2018 - April 2019
# VARIABLE DESCRIPTION: The 'ID'; 'Sex'; 'Length' variables correspond to the sample ID; sex; and snout-vent length of an individual bullfrog

# VARIABLE DESCRIPTION: The 'Ranavirus' columns containes whether the individual bullfrog tested positive (1) or negative (0) for Ranavirus; 'RV_viral-load' is the viral load; or amount of virus; in copies/ng of DNA

# VARIABLE DESCRIPTION: The 'Acantho' to 'Pentastomida_larva' columns contain counts of helminth parasites identified and assigned to either Acanthocephala; Nematoda; Trematoda; Cestoda; Pentastomida (respectively); 'Total_abund' and 'Total_rich' are the total abundance and richness of helminth parasite taxa in the bullfrog
# MISSING DATA: NA values were given to missing values in the Sex; Length; and RV_viral-load variables
# DATA TRACK CHANGES LOG (use this section to record any changes to the data set after it is created)
# DATE:              # CHANGES:
# ----- END OF METADATA -----
# ----- START OF DATA -----
